abstract: Dr. Stephen Hahn was on Thursday confirmed as the new head of the U.S. Food and Drug Administration, taking charge at a regulatory agency that oversees products ranging from complex cancer drugs, to food, cosmetics and tobacco.
snippet: Dr. Stephen Hahn was on Thursday confirmed as the new head of the U.S. Food and Drug Administration, taking charge at a regulatory agency that oversees products ranging from complex cancer drugs, to food, cosmetics and tobacco.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Dr. Stephen Hahn was on Thursday confirmed as the new head of the U.S. Food and Drug Administration, taking charge at a regulatory agency that oversees products ranging from complex cancer drugs, to food, cosmetics and tobacco.
headline_main: Senate Confirms Stephen Hahn as New FDA Chief
headline_print_headline: Senate Confirms Stephen Hahn as New FDA Chief

abstract: Cory Booker will try to keep his presidential hopes alive by doubling down on the early voting state of Iowa, despite failing to qualify for next week's Democratic debate, his campaign said on Thursday.
snippet: Cory Booker will try to keep his presidential hopes alive by doubling down on the early voting state of Iowa, despite failing to qualify for next week's Democratic debate, his campaign said on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Cory Booker will try to keep his presidential hopes alive by doubling down on the early voting state of Iowa, despite failing to qualify for next week's Democratic debate, his campaign said on Thursday.
headline_main: Democrat Booker Doubling Down in Iowa After Failing to Make Debate
headline_print_headline: Democrat Booker Doubling Down in Iowa After Failing to Make Debate

abstract: The National Labor Relations Board has ruled in McDonald's favor in a long-running case filed by 20 workers who were fired or faced retaliation for trying to unionize.

headline_main: US Labor Board Rules for McDonald's in Unionization Case

abstract: - The U.S. House of Representatives on Thursday approved legislation aimed at driving down the prices that seniors pay for prescription drugs, but the bill's future is clouded by President Donald Trump's threat of a veto and lack of support in the Senate.
snippet: - The U.S. House of Representatives on Thursday approved legislation aimed at driving down the prices that seniors pay for prescription drugs, but the bill's future is clouded by President Donald Trump's threat of a veto and lack of support in the...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — - The U.S. House of Representatives on Thursday approved legislation aimed at driving down the prices that seniors pay for prescription drugs, but the bill's future is clouded by President Donald Trump's threat of a veto and lack of support in the Senate.
headline_main: Democrats Pass U.S. Bill to Lower Drug Prices That Trump Threatens to Veto
headline_print_headline: Democrats Pass U.S. Bill to Lower Drug Prices That Trump Threatens to Veto

abstract: Top Democrats and Republicans said they had an “agreement in principle” on $1.37 trillion in federal spending to keep the government funded through the end of the year.
snippet: Top Democrats and Republicans said they had an “agreement in principle” on $1.37 trillion in federal spending to keep the government funded through the end of the year.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senior lawmakers announced on Thursday that they had reached a tentative bipartisan agreement on funding the government for the remainder of the fiscal year, offering a solution to avert a shutdown after weeks of haggling over money for President Trump’s border wall and other matters.

abstract: It's been true for some time that Republicans are generally more hostile to the news media than Democrats, but a study released Thursday found that's much more the case for supporters of President Donald Trump.
snippet: It's been true for some time that Republicans are generally more hostile to the news media than Democrats, but a study released Thursday found that's much more the case for supporters of President Donald Trump.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — It's been true for some time that Republicans are generally more hostile to the news media than Democrats, but a study released Thursday found that's much more the case for supporters of President Donald Trump.
headline_main: Study Shows Hostility Toward Journalists by Trump Fans

abstract: The U.S. Senate on Thursday unanimously passed a resolution that recognizes as a genocide the mass killings of Armenians a century ago, a historic move that infuriated Turkey and dealt a blow to the already problematic ties between Ankara and Washington.
snippet: The U.S. Senate on Thursday unanimously passed a resolution that recognizes as a genocide the mass killings of Armenians a century ago, a historic move that infuriated Turkey and dealt a blow to the already problematic ties between Ankara and Wash...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. Senate on Thursday unanimously passed a resolution that recognizes as a genocide the mass killings of Armenians a century ago, a historic move that infuriated Turkey and dealt a blow to the already problematic ties between Ankara and Washington.
headline_main: U.S. Senate Passes Resolution Recognizing Armenian Genocide, Angering Turkey
headline_print_headline: U.S. Senate Passes Resolution Recognizing Armenian Genocide, Angering Turkey

abstract: The Pentagon on Thursday tested a conventionally configured ground-launched ballistic missile, a test that would have been prohibited under the Intermediate-range Nuclear Forces Treaty.
snippet: The Pentagon on Thursday tested a conventionally configured ground-launched ballistic missile, a test that would have been prohibited under the Intermediate-range Nuclear Forces Treaty.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Pentagon on Thursday tested a conventionally configured ground-launched ballistic missile, a test that would have been prohibited under the Intermediate-range Nuclear Forces Treaty.
headline_main: U.S. Tests Ground-Launched Ballistic Missile After INF Treaty Exit
headline_print_headline: U.S. Tests Ground-Launched Ballistic Missile After INF Treaty Exit

abstract: It was nighttime when Pedro Lucas came home, clutching receipts showing he had paid a funeral home to have the bodies of three immigrant laborers returned to Guatemala from Oregon.
snippet: It was nighttime when Pedro Lucas came home, clutching receipts showing he had paid a funeral home to have the bodies of three immigrant laborers returned to Guatemala from Oregon.
lead_paragraph: GERVAIS, Ore. — It was nighttime when Pedro Lucas came home, clutching receipts showing he had paid a funeral home to have the bodies of three immigrant laborers returned to Guatemala from Oregon.
headline_main: Crash Shines Light on Immigrants in Christmas Tree Workforce
headline_print_headline: Crash Shines Light on Immigrants in Christmas Tree Workforce
